        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You become living flame, giving you fire immunity, resistance 10 to precision damage, and weakness 5 to cold and to water. Any creature that touches you or damages you with an unarmed attack or non-reach melee weapon takes [[/r 3d6[fire]]] damage. Your unarmed attacks deal 1d4 additional fire damage, and your fire spells deal one additional die of fire damage (of the same damage die the spell uses). You can cast <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Produce Flame]</em> as an innate spell; the casting is reduced from 2 actions to 1. In fire form, you have a fly Speed of 40 feet and don't need to breathe.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spell-effects.Item.Spell Effect: Fiery Body]</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (9th)</strong> Creatures touching you take [[/r 4d6[fire]]] damage instead of 3d6, your unarmed attacks deal 2d4 additional fire damage, and you have a fly Speed of 60 feet.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spell-effects.Item.Spell Effect: Fiery Body (9th Level)]</p>"
